Commit Message:
Basic badge support with thresholds

Initial implementation. The Badge supports

* text backgrounds and text colors
* corner radiuses
* simple string thresholds
* instantiating badge templates with different configurations

Signed-off-by: Gunnar Strand <Gurra.Strand@gmail.com>

Split definition list to separate lines

Github does not support the enhanced definition list for Markdown, so
this change simple makes an empty line between each definition.

Signed-off-by: Gunnar Strand <Gurra.Strand@gmail.com>

Support target attribute for link

The "target" attribute for the link can now be set with the
`link_target` setting. If the the target is "_blank" then the
link also receives the rel="noopener noreferer" attribute. See

https://www.jitbit.com/alexblog/256-targetblank---the-most-underestimated-vulnerability-ever/

Closes #5 target for link

Signed-off-by: Gunnar Strand <Gurra.Strand@gmail.com>

Multi-threshold support

This is a non-backwards compatible change.

The `thresholds` setting is now a mapping of labels to value to
background colors:

    thresholds={'build': { 'SUCCESS': '#2c2', 'FAILURE': '#c22' },
               {'test': { 'SUCCESS': '#22c', 'FAILURE': '#860' }}

This allows one instance (or config) to generate badges for all label
types.

The `value_backgrounds` acts as a fallback if the label + value is not
found in the `thresholds` data structure:

    value_backgrounds={ 'SUCCESS': 'green', 'FAILURE': 'red' }

Closes #1 Multi-threshold support

Signed-off-by: Gunnar Strand <Gurra.Strand@gmail.com>

Ordered threshold levels

Implements ordering of thresholds and levels so that values between
thresholds are associated with the closes higher value.

Fixes some errors in the documentation with missing `to_html()` calls
in Threshold examples.

Closes #2 Comparing threshold support

Signed-off-by: Gunnar Strand <Gurra.Strand@gmail.com>

Program for simplifying making a release

Adds sbin/make_release.py which simplifies making releases by supporting
stepping version number, collecting commit and issues information,
pushing source, and uploading package to pypi.

Some documentation fixes.

Signed-off-by: Gunnar Strand <Gurra.Strand@gmail.com>

Shading support

Implements support for shading between colors when values are between
two different thresholds. Shading is enabled by setting the `shade`
configuration for a label to `True`

Corrected all examples in the documentation.

Close #3 Shading between thresholds
